description:
Lenore, the cute little dead girl, makes her long-awaited return with the release of issue #2 of Roman Dirge's cult comic, on sale February 16, 2011.

"He loved with a love that was more than love."

After years of shocking physical and mental abuse, extreme violence and unnecessary brutality , could Mr. Gosh’s feelings of unrequited love for Lenore have finally turned? Only time and the dark and twisted creative genius of Roman Dirge will tell.

Featuring more gruesomely grisly tales of Lenore and her demented menagerie of twisted friends, this second chapter in the rebirth of Lenore sees Mr. Gosh, Lenore's long-suffering unrequited paramour, take center stage.

Lenore #2 will be a must have for all fans of Lenore - not least because of the revelation of Lenore’s surname. To celebrate the return of Lenore, last year's hit issue #1 is being re-solicited with a brand new exclusive cover by Dirge!
name: Lenore

description:
Sailor Moon gets a makeover with an entirely new translation, Japanese style right-to-left reading, new artwork, and detailed translation notes in the bi-monthly re-release of the Sailor Moon manga series.

The first six volumes have been collected in a box set, and the second half of the series will be available in a set in fall 2013. When joined together the box set will form an image. Also planned for release is the Sailor Moon Short Stories collection.
